title: For Sale:  CZ 100 9mm Pistol CS-USA Custom Shop
location: Santa Fe, NM, New Mexico, United States
postcontent:
This was CZ's first 9mm polymer frame pistol. It's double action only and doesn't require or have a safety. Just grab it and squeeze the trigger. These pistols are noted for having horrible triggers and because of that people assume they are inaccurate. This one is different. It just came back a couple of months ago from the CZ-USA Custom Shop. They only have one gunsmith there who works on these, and I spoke to him. He was able to do a trigger job and a reliability fix on it. It now runs perfectly and has a great trigger and accuracy. I am easily able to shoot empty shotgun shells with it every time at 25-40 yards. Reliability is flawless as well. Just stage the trigger and squeeze for accuracy. Or just squeeze all the way through for fast shots or self defense. Really it's about as simple as that.

This is a lightweight poly framed pistol with CZ quality that is as good as Glock, Beretta, Springfield, etc. Frankly some people like me think they are better. It comes with two magazines and is in its original locking padded case. Condition is near perfect, and it is just a great pistol. 

So if this gun is so great then why am I selling it ? Simple. I am a rifleman and I collect vintage Finnish and Russian firearms. This will "turn into" another of those. I have a couple of self defense guns and usually don't carry concealed. So I just don't need this one. You can have it for what I paid for it - $300. But for you there is no tax, no CZ Custom bill, and no waiting for three weeks while CZ tunes it up. It is ready to go. I test fired 100 rounds through it to confirm reliability and the trigger job and the pistol runs perfectly. Zero malfunctions of any type and it is now more accurate than I am. Recoil is very light and manageable because of the famous CZ ergonomics, and the polymer frame.

If you want to check it out, contact me through Armslist with your number and I will call you. I used to put my number in these ads, but I got inundated with scam offers. So unfortunately I can't do that anymore. When you come see it, bring your cash because you are going to like it. It's small enough for a carry gun, and large enough for a home defense gun.

We will have to meet in Santa Fe because I work some crazy long hours. I can usually break free for a few minutes so we can meet at almost any time though.

Thanks for reading my very long winded ad. You will like this one.

Doby Pilgrim
Santa Fe, NM

title: Want To Buy:  WTB Colt New Service .45 Long
postcontent:
I am looking for a shooter grade Colt New Service revolver chambered in .45 [Long] Colt (NOT .45 ACP).  I don't care if it's a military M1909 or a civilian, as long as it is mechanically sound and a good shooter.  Would prefer an attractive example with honest wear and patina, it's OK if the blue is completely worn off, but I do not want an abused/neglected gun with rust/pitting/excessive scratches or gouges. But well worn with character is fine.  Don't care if it was refinished or re-parkerized, if it was done well.  Barrel should be uncut, 5.5" or 7.5".  

Willing to pay a reasonable price for a nice piece, exact amount subject to negotiation based on *documentable* rarity, condition/grade, etc.  I recently passed up on one on Gunbroker that went for $305, because it was just not quite high enough grade for what I'm looking for, and watched another slightly nicer one because the reserve price was too high. If you think yours is worth a grand or more, it's probably too nice for me. Something around $500-700 ballpark.

I'm primarily looking to pay cash, but if you want to trade let me know what you're looking for and if I have it I may consider trading it with cash if necessary to balance out the value.

postcontent:
Kel-Tec KSGBLK 12GA Tactical Shotgun 14rd. MSRP:$1090.91.
 The KSG (Kel-Tec Shotgun) is Kel-Tec CNCs first entry into the shotgun market. The size, shape, and design is similar to the currently available Kel-Tec RFB rifle, but the KSG ejects downward, instead of forward. The KSG weighs 6.9 lbs. and is as compact as legally possible with a 26.1 overall length and an 18.5 cylinder bore barrel. Even with this compact size, the internal dual tube magazines hold an impressive 14 rounds of 12 gauge 2.75 rounds in total (7 per tube). It can also reliably shoot shells as short as 1 3/4" up to the 2.75".
 This simple and reliable pump action feeds from either the left or right tube. The feed side is manually selected by a lever located behind the trigger guard.
 The pump includes an under picatinny rail for the mounting of a forward grip, a light, or a laser. The included top picatinny sight rail will accept many types of optics or iron sights. Forward and rear sling loops are built in, and a basic sling is included. The soft rubber butt pad helps to tame recoil.
 The KSG receiver is made from hardened steel and includes the magazine tubes which have been welded in place. The grip and stock assembly is made of glass reinforced nylon (Zytel) and is easily disassembled by pushing out 2 pins, which store in 2 holes in the grip when removed. The barrel and pump assembly is removed by loosening the 2 front magazine tube nuts with a coin and sliding the assembly forward.

FROM WILSON COMBAT SITE, RE: SEMI AUTO CARRIERS:
"NOTE-We offer both semi-auto and full-auto carriers.  The only difference between the two are the carrier weight and external profile.  The full-auto carrier is slightly heavier to provide more mass and lower cyclic rate that can benefit carbine length and shorter gas systems, short barreled/suppressed rifles and machineguns. The semi-auto carrier is slightly lighter to provide the least amount of recoil impulse for rifle length gas systems and its design makes reinstalling the firing pin easier after cleaning.

Both carrier types are considered completely interchangeable and there are no restrictions on the ownership of a full auto carrier group in a semi automatic rifle.

The front part of the firing pin is blocked from any forward movement until the trigger is pulled completely back.
